{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","data":{"alias":"soppy-petit-alleycat","description":"## Why\n\n`verify.require_signature_for_close` (default False, OFF in this project) is the\n\"signature close gate\" — it requires an HMAC signature BEFORE closing a work ticket.\nIt is documented as the ALTERNATIVE to `require_completion_verification_for_close`,\nwhich is what THIS project actually uses (enabling both deadlocks a non-force close).\nIt has never been used here and is a retired alternative. Remove it and the close-gate\ncode reachable ONLY through it.\n\n## What\n\nDelete (reachable only via this gate):\n- `resolve_signature_gate` — `_commands/gates.py:58-80` (whole function).\n- `_signature_gate` — `_commands/txn.py:311-410` (whole function) + its two CommandErrors\n  (\"requires a certified signature (verdict: …)\" and the \"made at a different commit\"\n  HEAD-binding error).\n- `transition_core` plumbing: the `sig_require`/`sig_config_error` locals + the\n  `resolve_signature_gate` call (`txn.py:182-187`) and the story/epic close-gate block\n  (`txn.py:250-260`).\n- Config field + validator (`_config_schema.py:210`, `:485`).\n- True-path tests: `test_signature.py:312`, `test_close_gate_story_epic.py:38,116`,\n  `test_idea_close_bypass.py:27` (rewrite — bypass logic changes); trim flag-specific\n  assertions in `test_config_typed.py`, `test_config_perf.py`, `test_config_backcompat.py`;\n  regenerate golden CLI help (`transition__*help.out`).\n\n## Scope — MUST PRESERVE\n\nThe entire shared HMAC signing/attestation substrate: `signing.py` (`signing_key`,\n`verify_record`, `most_recent_attestation`, `head_sha`, `verify_signature`), the\n`attestations` map, `sign_manifest`/`verify_signature` MCP tools, and the\ncompletion-verifier close path (`transition_close.py`) + plan-review claim gate — all\nshare this machinery and must keep working. `--force-close` and `--verdict-hash` are\nNOT owned by this gate — keep both. Docs handled by the doc-sweep story.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `require_signature_for_close` removed from schema, parser, and any docs/help (coordinated with the doc-sweep story).\n- [ ] `resolve_signature_gate` and `_signature_gate` deleted; the story/epic close path no longer references a signature gate.\n- [ ] Shared signing machinery intact: plan-review claim gate and completion-verifier close gate both still function (prove with their existing tests green).\n- [ ] `--force-close` / `--verdict-hash` unaffected; true-path tests removed/rewritten; golden help regenerated.\n- [ ] `make lint && make typecheck && make test` pass.","id":"28f1-0ef8-65a4-4943","parent_id":"8d27-7ee1-f137-4b88","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Retire verify.require_signature_for_close and its dead close-gate code"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783967945779857001,"uuid":"6c764403-36a9-4d5e-bde9-8d589caeeb38"}